[normal]1.4 Creative Skillset has had a long and positive partnership with the BBC which involves t
[normal]he corporation at different levels: governance, research and consultation on training solutions, training funds, qualifications, accreditation of courses, industry clusters across the UK. A summary of the main areas of this partnership is outlined in Appen
[normal]dix 2, with some recent examples of our joined work. The BBC contributes financially to the core bu
[normal]dget of Creative Skillset, and 
[normal]to the TV Freelance Training Fund. It also invests directly 
[normal]in
[normal] the workforce engaged by the corporation through the BBC Academ
[normal]y, its training division, and co-invests by offering Apprenticeships. Both Creative Skillset and the BBC are part of the Creative Industries Council and BBC Academy is part of the CIC Skills group, as well as its sub-groups. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.5 Creative Skillset’s partn
[normal]ership with the BBC is formally described in a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) which was signed in June 2007, f
[normal]ollowing the new terms of the BBC Charter and Framework Agreement. 
[normal]The BBC/Creative Skillset MoU has had a positive impact in driving forward t
[normal]he partnership and Creative Skillset recognises the excellent work and efforts by the current director of BBC Academy (established in 2009) to fulfil the BBC obligations 
[normal]and to develop the partnership
[normal].
