[normal]We will expect that the BBC in its future form will continue to be the model of a creative employer that invests in and supports the people it engages (employee
[normal]s, freelancers, talent and craft professionals, managers and executives) as well as the people of the sector that it serves.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3
[normal].5 
[normal]There are still areas where the industry suffers from skills gaps and
[normal] there are
[normal] issues of fair access and mobility in these in
[normal]dustries for people from diverse backgrounds. 
[normal]As
[normal] the single biggest employer in the creative media and in receipt of the License Fee, the BBC has a role to play in addressing talent development and key skills 
[normal]issues for the creative economy and also
[normal] be 
[normal]accountable for its contribution.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3
[normal].
[normal]6
[normal] As above, we answer this on 
[normal]specific public pur
[normal]poses: we think that the BBC has made
[normal] a 
[normal]big and 
[normal]positive impac
[normal]t and 
[normal]contribution to these purposes
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]However, as 
[normal]seen from the evidence 
[normal]of
[normal] the BBC’s reporting on its tr
[normal]aining obligations, the reduction
[normal] of investment
[normal] in training
[normal] has seen its training budget almost halved in the last three years; this
[normal] will need to be addressed by 
[normal]the co
[normal]rporation and the BBC Trust, as it affects frontline delivery of key industry skill needs and could impact on the ability to produce quality content. 
[normal]In our view, the BBC does not calibrate investment towards the analysi
[normal]s of need.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.7 We would expect that the BBC Trust will fulfill its obligation on monitoring BBC Training output to consider the industry-wide impact, as it is stated in the Framework Agreement. We would like to remind the Trust that they should consult in
[normal]dustry
[normal]-wide
[normal] stakeholders beyond the BBC staff on the BBC Governance decisions on Training, as they are also ones to be affected.
[normal]&#xa0;
