[normal]3.9 Our rem
[normal]it relates only to
[normal] skills and talent and
[normal] 
[normal]we
[normal] can only comment on these issues and from that perspective.
[normal] 
[normal]A
[normal]s we mentioned before, 
[normal]we would like
[normal] to point the importance for the BBC to maintain investment and interest in the industry-wide training, as a responsibl
[normal]e producer and commissioner. The BBC
[normal] uses
[normal] freelancers
[normal] and 
[normal]its output includes programmes made by the independent sector, therefore it 
[normal]can
[normal] benefit from the industry-wide skills and tale
[normal]nt pool, as well as promote high-quality standards of output.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]3.10
[normal] 
[normal]We believe that the whole industry should 
[normal]invest in innovation and innovative new technologies. There is a strong business case for that, as the industries themselves are fast changing due to developing technologies. Innova
[normal]tion also comes with the need for
[normal] new skillsets, therefore investment in te
[normal]chnology should also consider investment in industry-wide training and n
[normal]ew pathways. In our opinion the BBC should
[normal] play their part in this.
